											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> ARMOR OF RO </td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'>
<P>The Armour of Ro requires the Paladin to combine 
Ronium and the correct mold to create the Armour of Ro.  There are various molds 
you must get from the Paladin Encampment in the Rathe Mountains.  Once you 
complete the Quests for the molds, you must gather the components to create the 
Ronium required. </P>
<P>Lord Thomas Searfire, in the Temple of Solusek Ro, 
will tell you what you must do.  You must have good faction with Lord Thomas to 
get him to talk to you.  To increase faction with Lord Thomas, travel to the 
Southern Desert of Ro and you can do one of two things.  Give Ortallius, an Orc, 
Dervish Rings, taken from Cutthroats, or give Rathmana money by playing his 
game. </P>
<P>Once you have high enough faction with Lord Thomas, 
ask him about the 'Bar of Alloy' and he will give you a Cauldron to forge 
Ronium.  Ronium requires 5 components that are spread throughout 
Norrath. </P>
<P>Ronium requires :</P>
<ul>
  <li>2 Bars of <b> Enchanted Platinum</b> - you purchase Platinum 
bars from a jeweller NPC.  An Enchanter, level 34 and above can enchant the 
platinum for you.</li>
  <li><b>Melatite</b> - found on Gnomebots in Solusek A.  The 
models that drop Melatite most frequently are MC, XC and MB.</li>
  <li><b>Mistmoore Granit</b>e - found on Gargoyles in Mistmoore 
Castle.   The Gargoyles near the Butler and Maid seem to have the highest rate 
of drop.</li>
  <li><b>Sands of Ro</b> - found on Sand Giants in Oasis or the 
Desert of Southern Ro. </li>
  <li><b>Soil of Underfoot </b> - must be made by Priestess Ghalea 
from the Dwarven city of Kaladim.  You must have high enough faction.  Give her 
four portions of Fairy Dust and she will turn them into Soil of 
Underfoot. </li>
</ul>
<P>Once you have Ronium and the mold, go to a forge, 
put in one bar of Ronium and your mold.  It seems the Blacksmith component of 
the Quest has been removed and you no longer require a Blacksmithing skill to 
forge the Armour.  To be on the safe side, get your Blacksmithing up to 35 or 40</P></td>
</tr>
